Bring a #large pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil.

Once boiling, add @Penne Pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4 servings), then drain.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise
into 1-inch-long pieces. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Mince @Chives{1/4%ounce}. Zest and
quarter @Lemon{1}.

== Crispy Panko Topping ==

Melt 1 TBSP @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and @Almonds{1/2%ounce}; season with @Salt{} and
@Pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Stir in a pinch of lemon zest and a pinch of @Chili Flakes{1%teaspoon}.
Transfer to a #small bowl{}.

== Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add
asparagus and cook, stirring often, until bright green and tender,
~{2-4%minutes}.

Add tomato and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season
with salt and pepper.

== Pasta ==

Add drained penne, @Garlic Herb Butter{2%tablespoon}, half the @Parmesan Cheese{1/4%cup}
(save the rest for serving), and 1⁄3 cup reserved pasta cooking water
(½ cup for 4 servings) to pan with veggies; stir until thoroughly combined.
Season with salt and pepper.

Add half the chives, remaining lemon zest, 1 TBSP plain butter (2 TBSP for 4
servings), and as many remaining chili flakes as you like to pan with pasta.
Cook, stirring, until everything is thoroughly coated in sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time.

Turn off heat; stir in a squeeze of lemon juice to taste. Taste and season with
salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide pasta between bowls. Sprinkle with panko mixture and remaining Parmesan.
Add a drizzle of olive oil over bowls. Garnish with remaining chives and serve
with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.